The paper deals with routing algorithms on Delaunay triangulations, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm presented is deterministic and local, which suggests that it involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of Schnyder's embedding scheme, which is a technique used in network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI). The concept of routing is also relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and social networks (cs.SI).
